%% Update planning: compiler decision flowchart
%% Shows how the compiler chooses between delta and full rebuild,
%% and the steps within each strategy.

flowchart TD
    A[New AclTable arrives] --> B[Diff old vs new table]
    B --> C{Changed rules k}

    C -->|k = 0| D[No-op: tables are identical]

    C -->|k small| E[Delta Strategy]
    C -->|k large or k/n > threshold| F[Full Rebuild Strategy]

    %% Delta strategy
    E --> E1[Compile delta from k changed rules]
    E1 --> E2{Choose delta backend}
    E2 -->|k ≤ 10| E3[LinearClassifier delta]
    E2 -->|k > 10| E4[DPDK ACL delta]
    E3 --> E5[Assemble Cascade: delta, old_base]
    E4 --> E5
    E5 --> E6[Atomic swap root pointer]
    E6 --> E7[Packets now two-tier]
    E7 --> E8[Background: compile_full new_table]
    E8 --> E9[Atomic swap to merged single-tier]
    E9 --> E10[Free old two-tier after drain]
    E10 --> Z[Done: steady state]

    %% Full rebuild strategy
    F --> F1[compile_full new_table]
    F1 --> F2[Atomic swap root pointer]
    F2 --> F3[Free old classifier after drain]
    F3 --> Z

    %% Styling
    style D fill:#9f9,stroke:#333
    style Z fill:#9f9,stroke:#333
    style E fill:#ff9,stroke:#333
    style F fill:#f99,stroke:#333
